{"lemma":"رَهْطِ","slug":"رَهْطِ","root":"ر.ه.ط","root_slug":"ر-ه-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ه-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَهْط","root":"رهط","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16860","n16861"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to gobble, to gulp greedily"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tribe, band, family, group, troop, cohort, squad"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Of imitative origin.\n\nBorrowed from Classical Syriac ܪܗܛܐ (rahṭā, rehṭā, “course; coordination; manner of living”)."},"ipa":["/ra.ha.tˤa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16860","headword_ar":"رَهْطٌ","root":"rhT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahaTN","text_ar":"رَهَطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, Msb, K,) but the former is the more chaste, (Lth, Msb,) A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tribe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearer relations:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [i. e. his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near kinsfolk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a number of men less than ten, among whom is no woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, Msb, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarN","text_ar":"نَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AZ, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from seven to ten;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, Msb, K;) and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little more;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd;) less than seven, to three, being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarN","text_ar":"نَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from three to ten:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iyrapN","text_ar":"عَشِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISk, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more than ten, to forty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, IF, Msb:) a pl., (S, Msb,) or a word having a pl. meaning, (Th, Az, Msb,) without any proper sing.; (Th, Az, S, Msb, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarN","text_ar":"نَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEo$arN","text_ar":"مَعْشَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iyrapN","text_ar":"عَشِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; all applied to men, exclusive of women: (Th, Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urohuwTN","text_ar":"اُرْهُوطٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (ISh, TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rhT","text_ar":"رهط"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohuTN","text_ar":"اَرْهُطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohiTapN","text_ar":"اَرْهِطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohaATN","text_ar":"اَرْهَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [all pls. of pauc.,] the last of these being pl. either of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahaTN","text_ar":"رَهَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahoTN","text_ar":"رَهْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAhiTu","text_ar":"اَرَاهِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, ISd, K,) as though pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohuTN","text_ar":"اَرْهُطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, ISd,) though Sb makes it pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahoTN","text_ar":"رَهْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because of the rareness of the pl. pl., (ISd,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAhiyTu","text_ar":"اَرَاهِيطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is app. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohaATN","text_ar":"اَرْهَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo rahoTuhu dinoyapF","text_ar":"هُمْ رَهْطُهُ دِنْيَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are his people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his tribe, closely related."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And it is said in the Kur [xxvii. 49],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wakaAna qiY Almadiynapi tisoEapu rahoTK","text_ar":"وَكَانَ قِى المَدِينَةِ تِسْعَةُ رَهْطٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) but this means, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And there were in the city"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nine persons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nine men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel.) ―         -b2-  You also say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahoTN mino Eu$arK","text_ar":"رَهْطٌ مِنْ عُشَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A collection of plants of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$r","text_ar":"عشر"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAar, Sh, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ayk","text_ar":"ايك"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An enemy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaduw~N","text_ar":"عَدُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA; [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eadow","text_ar":"عَدْو"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) mentioned by Sgh, on the authority of Ibn- 'Abbád. (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a waistwrapper"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaAr","text_ar":"اـِزَار"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of leather,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jm,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sides"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1170},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which are slit in several places in their lower parts, so that one may walk in it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jm, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wool;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Tálib the Grammarian;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a skin of Et-Táïf, slit in several places;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a skin of a size equal to the space between the navel and the knee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a skin slit into a number of thongs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strips;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, S, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a skin cut into a number of thongs"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strips, these being one above another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a waist-wrapper"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miy^ozar","text_ar":"مِيْزَر"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leather, slit in several places, except in the place of the pudendum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a skin slit into strips, each strip being of the breadth of four fingers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn by children,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a young girl before she has arrived at puberty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a woman in menstruis:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, S, M, K, &c.:) [in Nubia, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahoT","text_ar":"رَهْط"},{"kind":"text","text":", still called by that name, is very neatly made, consisting of a great number of slender thongs: it is worn there by young girls, and is generally their only covering, completely surrounding and concealing the pelvic portion of the body, and the whole or part of the thighs:] in the Time of Ignorance, the men used to perform their circuitings [around the Kaabeh] naked, and the women wearing [only] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rhT","text_ar":"رهط"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawofN","text_ar":"حَوْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places:] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohaATN","text_ar":"اَرْهَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] (S, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rihaATN","text_ar":"رِهَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISh, S, K:) or this last is a sing. also, (K,) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of leather of a size equal to the space between the place of the waist-band and the knee, slit in several places like the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thongs called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruk","text_ar":"شُرُك"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sandal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iraAk","text_ar":"شِرَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"worn by a girl of seven years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment worn by the boys of the Arabs of the desert, consisting of overlapping folds"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plies, one above another, like fans:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arohiTapN","text_ar":"اَرْهِطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.]. (K.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","Msb","K","S","AZ","ISk","As","IF","Th","Az","ISh","TA","ISd","Bd","Jm","M","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n16861","headword_ar":"رَهَطٌ","root":"rhT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahoTN","text_ar":"رَهْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}